1e:["$","h2","18",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"1. Microsoft Copilot Studio (Market Share: 38.6%)"}]
1f:["$","p","20",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Best for:"}]," Organizations already invested in Microsoft 365 and Azure."]}]
20:["$","p","22",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Microsoft has the largest market share in the agent orchestration space — 38.6% according to VB Pulse data. Copilot Studio lets you build custom AI agents that integrate natively with SharePoint, Dynamics 365, Teams, and the broader M365 ecosystem."]}]
21:["$","p","24",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I like:"}]," The ecosystem integration is unmatched. An agent built in Copilot Studio can natively access SharePoint documents, book meetings through Teams, pull CRM data from Dynamics 365, and trigger Power Automate workflows — without any custom connectors. The security model inherits your existing Microsoft 365 permissions. VB Pulse data shows enterprises cite security and permissions as the #1 buying criterion, and Microsoft's existing infrastructure makes this easy."]}]
22:["$","p","26",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I don't like:"}]," You're locked into the Microsoft ecosystem. If your company uses Google Workspace or Slack heavily, Copilot Studio agents can't natively integrate with those. The agent capabilities are less flexible than OpenAI's or Anthropic's offerings — you can't easily run custom models or complex multi-step reasoning workflows. Pricing is also opaque for standalone usage."]}]
23:["$","p","28",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Real user feedback:"}]," G2 reviewers note high satisfaction with integration capabilities (89%) but lower marks for customization flexibility (72%). One enterprise architecture director noted, \"Copilot Studio is perfect if you're all-in on Microsoft. If you're not, it creates as many problems as it solves.\""]}]
24:["$","p","30",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Pricing:"}]," Included with Microsoft 365 E3/E5 licenses. Standalone starts at $200/month for 100 agent conversations."]}]
25:["$","h2","32",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"2. OpenAI Agents SDK (Market Share: 25.7%)"}]
26:["$","p","34",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Best for:"}]," Teams building custom, model-first agent workflows."]}]
27:["$","p","36",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["OpenAI holds the second-largest market share at 25.7%. The Agents SDK (launched in March 2026) allows developers to create multi-agent systems with guardrails, handoffs between agents, and Python-based orchestration logic."]}]
28:["$","p","38",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I like:"}]," The model quality is the best available. GPT-5's reasoning capabilities mean your agents actually handle complex, multi-step tasks without hallucinating as frequently as alternatives. The SDK's handoff mechanism — where specialized sub-agents pass control to each other — is architecturally elegant. The Python-first approach means your dev team can integrate agents into existing codebases without learning a new DSL."]}]
29:["$","p","40",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I don't like:"}]," Self-hosting is basically impossible for large-scale deployments — you're running entirely on OpenAI's infrastructure. Costs can spiral. VB Pulse found enterprises are increasingly concerned about data sovereignty with OpenAI's cloud-only model. The security model is simpler than Microsoft's (project-based API keys vs. full role-based access control)."]}]
2a:["$","p","42",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Real user feedback:"}]," Developer satisfaction on Hacker News and Reddit is high for the SDK's flexibility, but enterprise buyers on G2 give lower marks for compliance certifications (73%). A VP of Engineering at a FinTech company reported, \"The agent SDK is brilliant for prototyping. But productionizing at scale requires building your own security and monitoring layer.\""]}]
2b:["$","p","44",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Pricing:"}]," Pay-per-token. GPT-5 agents: $15/million input tokens, $60/million output tokens. Estimate $0.05-0.50 per complex agent conversation."]}]
2c:["$","h2","46",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"3. Anthropic Claude Enterprise (Market Share: 5.7% — Fastest Growing)"}]
2d:["$","p","48",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Best for:"}]," Security-conscious enterprises handling sensitive data."]}]
2e:["$","p","50",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Anthropic's market share jumped from 0% to 5.7% in Q1 2026, making it the fastest-growing agent orchestration platform. Claude Enterprise emphasizes constitutional AI, human-in-the-loop approval workflows, and granular permission controls that VB Pulse says are now the #1 enterprise buying criterion."]}]
2f:["$","p","52",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I like:"}]," The security-first architecture is genuinely differentiated. Claude Enterprise allows admins to define guardrails at every level: which data the agent can access, which actions require human approval, and which domains the agent is allowed to operate in — all enforced at the infrastructure level, not just the prompt level. The tool use (function calling) API is the most reliable I've tested, with fewer parsing errors than alternatives."]}]
30:["$","p","54",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I don't like:"}]," The platform is newer and the ecosystem is smaller. Fewer pre-built integrations, a smaller community, and less published documentation for complex multi-agent scenarios than Microsoft or OpenAI. The 5.7% market share reflects that many enterprises are still evaluating rather than deploying at scale."]}]
31:["$","p","56",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Real user feedback:"}]," Early enterprise adopters praise the safety features. A CISO at a healthcare SaaS company noted, \"Claude Enterprise is the first agent platform our compliance team approved for handling PHI.\" But developers note the learning curve — one senior ML engineer said, \"Setting up granular guardrails is powerful but time-consuming. Expect 2-3 weeks of configuration before your first production agent.\""]}]
32:["$","p","58",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Pricing:"}]," Custom — typically $100-500/seat/month depending on usage. Enterprise tier requires annual commitment."]}]
33:["$","h2","60",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"4. Sierra (Pre-Launch — $950M in Funding)"}]
34:["$","p","62",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Best for:"}]," Customer service agent automation at scale."]}]
35:["$","p","64",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Founded by Bret Taylor (former Salesforce co-CEO), Sierra raised $950M in May 2026 to build the definitive enterprise agent platform for customer service. The company claims their agents can handle 80%+ of customer support interactions autonomously."]}]
36:["$","p","66",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I like:"}]," The focus on customer service specifically means the product is purpose-built, not a general platform you need to customize. Sierra claims 94% customer satisfaction on agent-handled conversations — comparable to human agents. Their stance on transparency means all interactions are logged, and the agent clearly identifies itself as AI."]}]
37:["$","p","68",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I don't like:"}]," It's not launched yet at general availability. The niche focus means it can't be used for non-customer-service use cases. The funding round was so large that expectations are incredibly high — any misstep will be magnified."]}]
38:["$","p","70",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Pricing:"}]," TBD (not yet publicly announced)."]}]
39:["$","h2","72",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"5. Google Vertex AI Agent Builder (Market Share: ~12%)"}]
3a:["$","p","74",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Best for:"}]," Multi-modal agent use cases with Google Cloud infrastructure."]}]
3b:["$","p","76",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Google's entry into the agent orchestration space focuses on integrating voice, text, image, and video into single agent workflows. It's particularly strong for knowledge retrieval and enterprise search scenarios."]}]
3c:["$","p","78",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I like:"}]," The multi-modal capabilities are unique — agents can process images, analyze videos, and search across your entire Google Workspace simultaneously. Integration with BigQuery and Google's data infrastructure means agents can answer complex analytics questions natively. Vertex AI's pricing model ($0.07/agent/hour) is more predictable than per-token models."]}]
3d:["$","p","80",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I don't like:"}]," The agent orchestration capabilities lag behind Microsoft and OpenAI in sophistication. Multi-step reasoning and agent handoffs are less mature. The Google Cloud ecosystem, while strong for data, has weaker enterprise SaaS integration than Microsoft's."]}]
3e:["$","p","82",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Pricing:"}]," $0.07/agent/hour plus model usage costs. Enterprise contracts available."]}]
3f:["$","h2","84",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"6. AWS Bedrock Agents (Market Share: ~10%)"}]
40:["$","p","86",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Best for:"}]," AWS-native enterprises with strict compliance requirements."]}]
41:["$","p","88",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["AWS Bedrock Agents leverage Amazon's enterprise infrastructure strengths — VPC isolation, SOC 2/HIPAA/FedRAMP compliance, and deep integration with AWS services like S3, Lambda, and DynamoDB."]}]
42:["$","p","90",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I like:"}]," For enterprises in regulated industries, Bedrock Agents offer the strongest compliance posture. You can deploy agents entirely within your VPC with no data leaving your network (using the Bedrock VPC endpoint). Knowledge bases can be stored entirely in S3 with your encryption keys. Integration with AWS IAM means you can use existing permission models."]}]
43:["$","p","92",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I don't like:"}]," The agent capabilities are basic compared to the leaders. The platform supports single-agent scenarios well but multi-agent coordination is limited. Developers complain about the complexity — one DevOps engineer noted, \"Deploying a simple agent requires navigating 8 different AWS services and writing CloudFormation templates.\""]}]
44:["$","p","94",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Pricing:"}]," $0.10/agent/hour. Additional costs for foundation model usage."]}]
45:["$","h2","96",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"7. Fin by Intercom — Meta-Agent Management"}]
46:["$","p","98",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Best for:"}]," Existing Intercom customers who want AI customer support agents."]}]
47:["$","p","100",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Intercom's Fin recently introduced a meta-agent feature — an agent whose sole job is managing other AI agents. It monitors agent performance, escalates misbehaving agents to human supervisors, and orchestrates complex workflows across multiple specialized agents."]}]
48:["$","p","102",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I like:"}]," The meta-agent concept is genuinely innovative — it solves the very real problem of \"who watches the watchers\" in multi-agent deployments. For Intercom customers, this is a straightforward upgrade with zero migration cost. The monitoring capabilities are production-ready, providing dashboards of agent accuracy, handoff rates, and user satisfaction per agent."]}]
49:["$","p","104",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"What I don't like:"}]," It only works within the Intercom ecosystem. You can't use Fin's meta-agent to manage OpenAI agents or custom-built agents. The pricing structure requires an existing Intercom subscription."]}]
4a:["$","p","106",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Pricing:"}]," Included with Fin plans ($39/agent/month + usage)."]}]
4b:["$","h2","108",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Key Decision Factors"}]
4c:["$","h3","110",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Security & Permissions (Now the #1 Criterion)"}]
4d:["$","p","112",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["VB Pulse data clearly shows that security and granular permissions have overtaken model quality as the top enterprise buying criterion for agent orchestration platforms. This explains Anthropic's rapid growth — their constitutional AI and granular guardrails resonate with compliance teams, even if the model isn't the most capable."]}]
4e:["$","h3","114",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Build vs. Buy"}]
4f:["$","div","table-124",{"className":"overflow-x-auto mb-6","children":["$","table",null,{"className":"w-full text-sm border-collapse","children":[["$","thead",null,{"children":["$","tr",null,{"className":"bg-[#162440]","children":[["$","th","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#3B82F6] border-b border-[#1E3A5F]","children":"Factor"}],["$","th","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#3B82F6] border-b border-[#1E3A5F]","children":"Build In-House"}],["$","th","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[#3B82F6] border-b border-[#1E3A5F]","children":"Buy Agent Platform"}]]}]}],["$","tbody",null,{"children":[["$","tr","0",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Time to deployment"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"3-6 months (SDK + infra)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Days to weeks"}]]}],["$","tr","1",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Customization"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Complete control"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Platform constraints"}]]}],["$","tr","2",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Security ownership"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Your responsibility"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Shared responsibility"}]]}],["$","tr","3",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Maintenance burden"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Full team required"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Handled by platform"}]]}],["$","tr","4",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Scalability"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Must build infra"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Built-in"}]]}],["$","tr","5",{"className":"border-b border-[#1E3A5F]/50 hover:bg-[#162440]/50 transition-colors","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Cost"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Higher upfront, variable ongoing"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"px-4 py-3 text-[#8BA3BE]","children":"Subscription + usage"}]]}]]}]]}]}]
50:["$","h3","125",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Ecosystem Lock-In"}]
51:["$","p","127",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Your choice of agent orchestration platform will heavily influence your broader enterprise software strategy. Microsoft, Google, and AWS all use their agent platforms as ecosystem anchors. If you're evaluating a multi-cloud strategy, consider the agent platform as an important — or potentially decisive — factor."]}]
52:["$","h2","129",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"The Bottom Line"}]
53:["$","p","131",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["The enterprise AI agent orchestration market is still in its early stages, but the battle lines are clear:"]}]
54:["$","p","133",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["- ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Choose Microsoft Copilot Studio"}]," if you're all-in on Microsoft 365 and want the fastest path to deploying agents with existing security infrastructure."]}]
55:["$","p","134",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["- ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Choose OpenAI Agents SDK"}]," if model quality and developer flexibility are your top priorities — but budget for building your own security layer."]}]
56:["$","p","135",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["- ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Choose Anthropic Claude Enterprise"}]," if you're in a regulated industry and security/compliance is non-negotiable. It's the fastest-growing player for a reason."]}]
57:["$","p","136",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["- ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Choose Google Vertex AI Agent Builder"}]," for multi-modal use cases where image, video, and data analysis are central to your agent workflows."]}]
58:["$","p","137",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["- ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Choose AWS Bedrock Agents"}]," for deployment entirely within your VPC in highly regulated environments."]}]
59:["$","p","138",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["- ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Consider Sierra"}]," for customer service automation once it reaches GA — but wait for production evidence."]}]
5a:["$","p","140",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["The market share shift from 0% to 5.7% for Anthropic in a single quarter signals something important: enterprises are voting with their budgets for security-first agent platforms. Expect this trend to accelerate through 2026."]}]
5b:["$","h2","142",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"FAQ"}]
5c:["$","h3","144",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"What is AI agent orchestration?"}]
5d:["$","p","145",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["AI agent orchestration refers to the platforms and tools that manage the lifecycle of AI agents in production — including deployment, monitoring, coordination between multiple agents, security enforcement, and human-in-the-loop oversight. It's the infrastructure layer that sits between LLM models and real enterprise workflows."]}]
5e:["$","h3","147",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Which platform has the best security for enterprise AI agents?"}]
5f:["$","p","148",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Anthropic Claude Enterprise currently offers the most granular security controls, including constitutional AI guardrails, human-in-the-loop approval workflows, and domain-level permissions. For enterprises needing VPC isolation and existing compliance certifications, AWS Bedrock Agents are the strongest choice."]}]
60:["$","h3","150",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"How much does enterprise AI agent orchestration cost?"}]
61:["$","p","151",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Pricing varies dramatically by platform. Microsoft Copilot Studio is included with E3/E5 licenses. OpenAI charges per-token ($15-60/million tokens). AWS and Google charge per-agent-hour ($0.07-0.10). Anthropic and Sierra use custom enterprise pricing. For a medium-sized enterprise (500 agents), expect $50K-200K/month depending on usage and platform."]}]
62:["$","h3","153",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Can I use multiple agent orchestration platforms together?"}]
63:["$","p","154",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Technically yes, but it adds significant complexity. Multi-agent workflows across platforms require custom middleware for coordination, which negates many benefits of using a platform. Most enterprises (68% according to VB Pulse) standardize on a single primary platform for the first 12 months."]}]
64:["$","h3","156",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"Is agent orchestration replacing traditional SaaS applications?"}]
65:["$","p","157",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["No. Agent orchestration platforms complement rather than replace traditional SaaS applications. They act as a coordination layer — directing AI agents to use your existing SaaS tools (CRM, ERP, ticketing systems) more effectively. The platforms that integrate deepest with existing enterprise tools (Microsoft, Google, AWS) have a strategic advantage here."]}]
66:["$","p","159",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Sources:"}]," VB Pulse Enterprise Agent Orchestration Report (Q2 2026), G2 Agent Platforms Grid (Spring 2026), TechCrunch Sierra Funding Coverage (May 2026), VentureBeat Anthropic Enterprise Coverage (May 2026), Product Hunt SaaS Category (May 2026), Hacker News Show (May 2026), platform documentation and pricing pages (accessed May 2026). All market share figures and ratings as of May 2026."]}]
